PROGRAM STRUCTURE – SMART CURRENCY CONVERTER
1. Packages & Imports

java.sql.* → Database connectivity (JDBC)

java.util.* → Scanner, List, Map, Collections

2. Interface
ConverterService

Declares convert() method.

Ensures any converter class must implement conversion logic.

3. Custom Exception
InvalidCurrencyException

Handles invalid currency codes.

Used when user enters unsupported currency.

4. Base Class (Abstraction)
RateProvider (abstract)

Contains a map of currency rates.

Abstract method loadRates().

Has method getRate() that throws exception if invalid.

5. Child Class (Inheritance + Polymorphism)
StaticRateProvider

Extends RateProvider.

Implements loadRates() with static currency values.

6. Service Class (Interface Implementation)
CurrencyConverter

Implements ConverterService.

Uses RateProvider (polymorphism).

Converts amount from one currency to another using USD as a base.

7. POJO Class
ConversionRecord

Represents a conversion transaction.

Used for Collection history and database storage.

8. Database Helper
DBHelper

Provides getConnection().

Stores DB URL, username, password.

9. DAO Layer (Database Operations)
ConversionDAO

Inserts conversion record into DB.

Uses JDBC PreparedStatement.

10. Multithreading
LoggerThread

Accepts list of conversion records.

Synchronized block ensures thread-safe logging.

Prints conversion logs in background.

11. Main Application
SmartCurrencyConverter (main class)

Creates Scanner.

Uses polymorphism → new CurrencyConverter(new StaticRateProvider())

Creates:

history (List of ConversionRecord)

ConversionDAO object

Takes user input:

amount

source currency

target currency

Performs:

Conversion

Adds record to list

Saves to database

Starts logging thread

Ends when amount entered is 0.
